WEBVTT

00:01.540 --> 00:03.420
♪♪

00:03.420 --> 00:05.670
[ Sighs ]

00:05.670 --> 00:07.500
No, no, Mom.
We've got this.

00:07.500 --> 00:08.790
Don't offer to help.

00:08.790 --> 00:10.080
Ah, way ahead of you.

00:10.080 --> 00:11.170
[ Door closes ]
[ Chuckles ]

00:11.170 --> 00:12.500
Why do you put off
getting your tree

00:12.500 --> 00:13.920
until the last second?

00:13.920 --> 00:15.460
It's almost Christmas.

00:15.460 --> 00:17.580
We wait so we get a better price
on the reject trees.

00:17.580 --> 00:19.790
Because a penny saved
is a penny embarrassing.

00:19.790 --> 00:21.960
This one
only cost us 15 bucks

00:21.960 --> 00:23.880
because it's infested
with termites.

00:23.880 --> 00:25.790
But here's a fun fact --
we're renters!

00:27.250 --> 00:28.790
Do you have to
keep walking around

00:28.790 --> 00:29.790
in that creepy thing?

00:29.790 --> 00:31.120
Yeah.
I do.

00:31.120 --> 00:32.500
I didn't get the lead
in "The Nutcracker,"

00:32.500 --> 00:34.710
so I'm stuck getting used to
this stupid Mouse King mask.

00:34.710 --> 00:37.540
Well, it's happening,
so suck it up.

00:37.540 --> 00:40.080
All I want this year
is a peaceful Christmas.

00:40.080 --> 00:42.420
All I want
is a Tiffany Infinity Bracelet.

00:42.420 --> 00:44.380
All I want
is an aging billionaire

00:44.380 --> 00:46.620
who has an aversion to pre-nups.
[ Chuckles ]

00:46.620 --> 00:47.920
Hmm.

00:47.920 --> 00:49.830
And all I want
for Christmas...

00:49.830 --> 00:52.880
[ Door closes ]
is for your mother
to leave.

00:52.880 --> 00:54.710
She's been here forever.
I want my office back.

00:54.710 --> 00:55.920
I'm tired of you guys
making fun of me

00:55.920 --> 00:56.920
whenever I want to
read a book.

00:56.920 --> 00:58.380
Books are for nerds,
nerd!

00:58.380 --> 00:59.380
[ Laughs ]

00:59.380 --> 01:01.000
[ Doorbell rings ]

01:03.620 --> 01:04.750
[ Gasps ] Daddy!

01:04.750 --> 01:06.580
Kitty-Kat!
[ Both laugh ]

01:06.580 --> 01:08.000
Children: Grandpa!

01:08.000 --> 01:10.500
Oh, hi, cutie.
Oh, hi, sweetheart.
[ Laughs ]

01:10.500 --> 01:11.580
Hey, pal.
How are you?
Hi.

01:11.580 --> 01:13.290
Why don't you take his bags
upstairs?

01:13.290 --> 01:14.250
Oh, yeah, grab that one
for me, would you?

01:14.250 --> 01:15.670
I didn't know
you were coming, Dad.

01:15.670 --> 01:18.330
Why didn't you call?
Well, I did.

01:18.330 --> 01:20.750
I told that little knucklehead
right there.

01:20.750 --> 01:23.750
Oh. Mom, Grandpa's coming
to town for Christmas.

01:24.960 --> 01:26.710
I love
that you came, Daddy.

01:26.710 --> 01:28.710
There is
just one hitch --

01:28.710 --> 01:29.750
Mom's here.

01:29.750 --> 01:31.540
She's still here?
Mm-hmm.

01:31.540 --> 01:33.210
I thought she would've
moved on by now.

01:33.210 --> 01:34.710
It's been months.
Thank you!

01:34.710 --> 01:36.120
Grandpa!

01:36.120 --> 01:37.620
Come put those presents
under the tree.

01:37.620 --> 01:39.120
[ Chuckles ]

01:39.120 --> 01:41.000
This is very,
very bad.

01:41.000 --> 01:43.500
We can't have my parents
in the same house.

01:43.500 --> 01:45.120
There's an understanding --
they only see each other

01:45.120 --> 01:46.420
at weddings
and funerals.

01:46.420 --> 01:48.170
It's been 25 years
since they split up.

01:48.170 --> 01:49.080
I'm sure they've moved on
by now.

01:50.080 --> 01:51.120
Marty?

01:55.210 --> 01:56.830
Hey, Kate.

01:56.830 --> 01:58.790
Nice ponytail.

01:58.790 --> 02:01.420
It's very "Last of the Mohicans"
meets "Cocoon."

02:01.420 --> 02:03.670
And how do you
look so good?

02:03.670 --> 02:07.250
Did you make a deal...
with yourself?

02:07.250 --> 02:08.330
[ Chuckles, snorts ]

02:08.330 --> 02:09.580
And I see that
you're still

02:09.580 --> 02:10.580
wearing cargo shorts.

02:10.580 --> 02:12.250
Oh, I'm sorry.

02:12.250 --> 02:13.960
I would have
gotten all dressed up

02:13.960 --> 02:16.380
had I known I was meeting
the Queen of England.

02:17.790 --> 02:20.120
Katie:
Well, deck the [bleep] halls.

02:25.540 --> 02:27.080
♪♪

02:29.380 --> 02:31.170
You don't have to
clear out of your room.

02:31.170 --> 02:32.790
I can just
sleep on the floor somewhere.

02:32.790 --> 02:34.120
Come on, Grandpa,

02:34.120 --> 02:35.920
you're not gonna
sleep on the floor.

02:35.920 --> 02:37.620
I'll just sleep
on Anna-Kat's pullout.

02:37.620 --> 02:39.170
Thanks, kiddo.

02:39.170 --> 02:41.000
Hey, I'm excited to go
see your dance thing.

02:41.000 --> 02:42.880
Don't get too excited.

02:42.880 --> 02:44.420
I didn't get
the starring role.

02:44.420 --> 02:46.710
I'm the Mouse King.
I wear a mask.

02:46.710 --> 02:48.040
No one will even
remember me.

02:48.040 --> 02:50.420
Hey.
Batman wore a mask.

02:50.420 --> 02:51.540
Superman wore a mask.

02:51.540 --> 02:52.620
Superman didn't
wear a mask.

02:52.620 --> 02:53.880
Batman wore a mask.

02:53.880 --> 02:55.420
What are you two
talking about?

02:55.420 --> 02:57.420
Uh, Grandpa was just
giving me some advice.

02:57.420 --> 03:01.420
Your grandpa is the best person
to go to for problems.

03:01.420 --> 03:03.540
He was a father
and a mother to me.
Marty: Aww.

03:03.540 --> 03:05.170
When these started
coming in strong...
I'm good.

03:05.170 --> 03:06.420
...I went to him.

03:06.420 --> 03:07.540
He took me to get my first bra.

03:07.540 --> 03:10.210
Most girls start
with a training bra.

03:10.210 --> 03:11.790
Not my Katie.
Still good.

03:11.790 --> 03:12.920
He also taught me
how to shave my legs.

03:12.920 --> 03:14.880
And how to change a flat,

03:14.880 --> 03:17.460
throw a curve ball,
and put on mascara.

03:17.460 --> 03:19.540
You got to flick your wrist
a little bit

03:19.540 --> 03:20.880
or it gets all clumpy.

03:20.880 --> 03:22.880
Why didn't Grandma
do this stuff with you?

03:22.880 --> 03:24.540
Because she found herself a job

03:24.540 --> 03:26.750
that would keep parenting
opportunities to a minimum.

03:29.290 --> 03:31.460
You don't have to
change the sheets for me.

03:31.460 --> 03:33.580
You do not want to sleep
in a 15-year-old boy's sheets.

03:33.580 --> 03:34.830
Mommmmm!

03:34.830 --> 03:36.460
You're right. I'm sorry, honey.

03:36.460 --> 03:38.670
You should also probably
wear flip-flops in the shower.

03:40.460 --> 03:42.000
Ugh!
I can't believe

03:42.000 --> 03:44.500
that you wrapped those presents
in aluminum foil.

03:44.500 --> 03:45.500
Why?

03:45.500 --> 03:47.170
You don't need tape,

03:47.170 --> 03:48.540
and a cutter
is right on the box.

03:48.540 --> 03:49.920
You don't have to
worry about scissors,

03:49.920 --> 03:51.540
and when you unwrap,
you can use it

03:51.540 --> 03:53.830
to cover your favorite
holiday leftovers.

03:53.830 --> 03:56.250
All right, this is why
your daughter

03:56.250 --> 03:57.670
buys last-minute
Christmas trees

03:57.670 --> 04:00.920
and reuses dryer sheets until
they dissolve into her clothing.

04:00.920 --> 04:02.880
Oh, you are a delight.

04:02.880 --> 04:04.170
Ugh.

04:04.170 --> 04:05.250
[ Sighs ]

04:05.250 --> 04:08.000
Well, looks like
our family Christmas

04:08.000 --> 04:09.620
is getting dragged
behind a dumpster

04:09.620 --> 04:11.750
and beaten with
a sack of batteries.

04:11.750 --> 04:13.460
You're just gonna have to ask
one of your parents to leave.

04:13.460 --> 04:15.250
I can't kick my parents out
on Christmas.

04:15.250 --> 04:16.750
The only thing
that we can do

04:16.750 --> 04:17.750
to have
a peaceful holiday

04:17.750 --> 04:18.790
is to keep them apart.

04:18.790 --> 04:20.000
I will take
my mom to work

04:20.000 --> 04:21.380
and you entertain my dad.

04:21.380 --> 04:22.620
What am I supposed to
do with him?

04:22.620 --> 04:24.620
He's a handyman.
Have him fix something.

04:24.620 --> 04:25.830
Fix what?
Nothing's broken.

04:28.380 --> 04:29.670
[ Cabinet clatters ]
There.

04:29.670 --> 04:30.670
Fix that.

04:30.670 --> 04:32.170
All right.

04:33.960 --> 04:35.790
[ Knock on door ]

04:39.880 --> 04:41.170
There's
the new understudy

04:41.170 --> 04:42.790
for the lead
of "Little Shop of Horrors."

04:42.790 --> 04:44.250
I couldn't have done it
without you.

04:44.250 --> 04:46.210
Ready to rehearse?
Let me just
grab my script.

04:49.880 --> 04:52.540
Hey, Pierce, do you wanna
play ponies with me?

04:52.540 --> 04:53.960
Ponies?
Yeah.

04:53.960 --> 04:55.040
I made up
a game called

04:55.040 --> 04:56.830
"Real Horsewives
of Connecticut."

04:56.830 --> 04:59.080
This is
Donatella Morningstar.

04:59.080 --> 05:01.620
She's having a launch party
for her new saddle line,

05:01.620 --> 05:04.420
but she didn't invite
Sparkles O'Donahue,

05:04.420 --> 05:07.420
so she's having lunch with
Bethany Trotsky to talk trash.

05:07.420 --> 05:09.250
Yeah,
I don't do ponies.

05:11.080 --> 05:13.540
Tell Mom and Dad
we're off to join the circus.

05:13.540 --> 05:15.500
Did you just come up with that
off the top of your head?

05:15.500 --> 05:16.920
Mm.
I can't believe
you haven't done improv.

05:16.920 --> 05:18.960
[ Giggles ]

05:18.960 --> 05:20.250
[ Door closes ]

05:20.250 --> 05:23.170
That boy needs
a hard hoof to the head.

05:23.170 --> 05:25.830
Ooo, Donatella,
you are bad.

05:27.670 --> 05:29.120
[ Grunts ]

05:29.120 --> 05:31.540
Nothing was ever good enough
for that woman.

05:31.540 --> 05:33.670
[ Glasses clack ]

05:35.460 --> 05:36.960
You have those
just loose in there?

05:36.960 --> 05:38.790
No bag?

05:38.790 --> 05:40.210
It's a pocket.
Why would I need a bag?

05:41.880 --> 05:43.540
Listen, I get that
she makes you nuts.

05:43.540 --> 05:44.670
She makes me nuts.

05:44.670 --> 05:47.330
But could you just
make peace with Kathryn?

05:47.330 --> 05:49.380
[ Laughs ]

05:49.380 --> 05:51.420
You see,
that would be like

05:51.420 --> 05:53.960
using a cement-based grout
on a joint

05:53.960 --> 05:55.120
instead of caulk.

05:55.120 --> 05:56.710
Ah.

05:56.710 --> 05:58.880
I'm saying
it wouldn't work.

05:58.880 --> 06:01.210
I'm just asking
for a small gesture.

06:01.210 --> 06:02.790
A peace offering.
Put on a pair of pants.

06:02.790 --> 06:04.000
My legs run hot!

06:04.000 --> 06:05.210
Listen,
all Katie wants

06:05.210 --> 06:06.460
is a stress-free
Christmas.

06:06.460 --> 06:08.460
Do it for your daughter
and your grandkids.

06:08.460 --> 06:10.750
All right.
I'll do it for them.

06:12.750 --> 06:15.170
Apple pie?

06:15.170 --> 06:16.170
How is it warm?

06:16.170 --> 06:18.040
I told you --
I run hot.
Mm.

06:18.040 --> 06:20.170
[ Indistinct conversations ]

06:20.170 --> 06:23.710
He wouldn't even play
"Real Horsewives" with me.

06:23.710 --> 06:25.920
That's crazy.
It's so fun.

06:25.920 --> 06:27.830
Did you offer him
Donatella Morningstar?

06:27.830 --> 06:29.290
She's the breakout star
of the whole show.

06:29.290 --> 06:30.710
[ Sighs ]
I didn't even have a chance.

06:30.710 --> 06:32.460
He just walked away.

06:32.460 --> 06:34.830
[ Sighs ] I get a bad feeling
from that guy.

06:34.830 --> 06:36.290
Me too.

06:36.290 --> 06:37.790
You need to get
your act together

06:37.790 --> 06:39.500
and win Taylor back.

06:39.500 --> 06:41.380
How?

06:41.380 --> 06:42.880
She's super mad.
She won't talk to me.

06:42.880 --> 06:44.000
It's Christmas.

06:44.000 --> 06:46.040
Put a Secret Santa gift
in her locker.

06:46.040 --> 06:48.000
Okay.
She won't know
it's from you,

06:48.000 --> 06:50.830
and when she loves it,
you pop out

06:50.830 --> 06:52.380
and do your
smiley handsome thing.

06:52.380 --> 06:53.920
I'm really good
at smiley handsome.

06:53.920 --> 06:55.710
Maybe the best
there ever was.

06:55.710 --> 06:56.920
But what do I get her?

06:56.920 --> 06:58.080
I happen to know she wants

06:58.080 --> 06:59.960
a Tiffany
Infinity Bracelet.

06:59.960 --> 07:01.580
All right.
I'm in.

07:01.580 --> 07:03.380
I just have
one question.
Mm-hmm.

07:03.380 --> 07:06.250
Did Donatella Morningstar
launch her new saddle line yet?

07:06.250 --> 07:08.710
She did.
And there was so much drama!

07:08.710 --> 07:09.830
[ Sighs ] I can't believe

07:09.830 --> 07:11.620
I missed it.
[ Chuckles ]

07:11.620 --> 07:13.880
♪♪

07:13.880 --> 07:16.880
Check it out --
the cabinet is fixed.

07:16.880 --> 07:19.210
And after my little talk
with your dad,

07:19.210 --> 07:20.210
so is Christmas.

07:20.210 --> 07:21.670
I wouldn't be so sure.

07:21.670 --> 07:23.380
Do you hear
them fighting?

07:23.380 --> 07:25.500
No, but they could have
sharpened candy canes

07:25.500 --> 07:26.580
and shivved each other.

07:26.580 --> 07:28.170
[ Footsteps ]
Oliver: Mom?

07:28.170 --> 07:30.250
Have you seen
my Mouse King mask?

07:30.250 --> 07:32.290
I saw it
in my office earlier.

07:32.290 --> 07:34.250
[ Chuckling ]
I'm fixing everything.

07:38.380 --> 07:39.920
Oh, dear.

07:40.960 --> 07:42.000
Ah.

07:43.080 --> 07:44.880
My mask!

07:44.880 --> 07:46.790
Oh, yeah, uh,
listen, kiddo, I'm sorry.

07:46.790 --> 07:48.960
It kind of got all squished
in the excitement.

07:48.960 --> 07:50.170
Oh.
Here, honey.

07:50.170 --> 07:52.170
Yeah, uh,
but I can fix it.

07:52.170 --> 07:54.080
Katie:
What is going on in there?

07:55.670 --> 07:59.330
Oh, my God.
What have you two done?

07:59.330 --> 08:01.120
Don't answer that.

08:01.120 --> 08:03.250
Please!
Don't answer that.

08:03.250 --> 08:05.500
Fine, I won't answer.

08:05.500 --> 08:07.830
But whatever did happen here
happened twice. [ Chuckles ]

08:07.830 --> 08:08.710
[ Sighs ]
Ugh!

08:15.040 --> 08:16.580
I told you
to keep them apart.

08:16.580 --> 08:18.540
They are the opposite
of apart, Greg!

08:18.540 --> 08:20.420
I wanted you to have
a peaceful Christmas.

08:20.420 --> 08:22.460
All I did was ask your dad
to put some pants on!
[ Sighs ]

08:22.460 --> 08:23.960
And I did.

08:23.960 --> 08:25.330
But then they came
right back off again.

08:25.330 --> 08:26.500
[ Chuckles ]

08:26.500 --> 08:28.750
I appreciated
the gesture.
Oh.

08:28.750 --> 08:30.000
You know, we just
started reminiscing

08:30.000 --> 08:31.210
about the good times,

08:31.210 --> 08:32.790
and one thing
led to another.

08:32.790 --> 08:34.080
And another.

08:34.080 --> 08:35.330
And most of the way
to another.

08:35.330 --> 08:37.250
Ugh.
Please stop.

08:37.250 --> 08:40.170
Your mother decided that maybe
we should give it another go.

08:40.170 --> 08:42.250
Yeah.
No.
Mnh-mnh.

08:42.250 --> 08:45.210
That is a terrible,
terrible idea.

08:45.210 --> 08:46.580
Right, Greg?
Terrible.

08:46.580 --> 08:48.250
[ Scoffs ]
We'll be fine.

08:48.250 --> 08:50.420
In fact, we're even thinking
about moving in together.

08:50.420 --> 08:52.380
Wait, not moving in together
in my office.

08:52.380 --> 08:53.380
An off-site location?

08:53.380 --> 08:54.380
My place.

08:54.380 --> 08:55.920
Hooray for love!

08:55.920 --> 08:57.620
[ Kathryn and Marty laugh ]

08:57.620 --> 09:02.210
♪♪

09:02.210 --> 09:03.790
I don't know
what my dad was thinking

09:03.790 --> 09:05.420
getting back together
with my mom.

09:05.420 --> 09:07.540
He doesn't remember
how awful she was to him.

09:07.540 --> 09:08.670
But I do.

09:08.670 --> 09:11.460
That's why I'm so easygoing
with Greg.

09:11.460 --> 09:14.420
Y-You are nicer to him than
you are other people, I guess.

09:14.420 --> 09:15.880
Katie,
they're both adults,

09:15.880 --> 09:17.620
and you get rid of your mom.
What's the big deal?

09:17.620 --> 09:19.120
Because the minute someone
better comes along,

09:19.120 --> 09:20.500
she is going to take off

09:20.500 --> 09:22.380
and break my dad's heart
all over again.

09:22.380 --> 09:24.380
That's cold.
You did the same thing
to your wife!

09:24.380 --> 09:26.380
That's right, because
a lesbian can do

09:26.380 --> 09:29.080
anything a heterosexual
can do, Doris.

09:29.080 --> 09:30.710
I can't watch my dad
go through it again.

09:30.710 --> 09:33.040
It took me a year
to get him back on his feet.

09:33.040 --> 09:34.580
It's probably why
I'm so nurturing.

09:34.580 --> 09:36.790
Wow. You really
see yourself differently

09:36.790 --> 09:37.920
than the rest of the world,
huh?

09:37.920 --> 09:39.080
Sounds like you have
to break them up

09:39.080 --> 09:39.830
before he gets
in too deep.

09:39.830 --> 09:41.710
I'd love to, but how?

09:41.710 --> 09:43.710
Do something to remind them why
they're so bad for each other.

09:43.710 --> 09:45.710
Find a trigger.

09:45.710 --> 09:47.830
Like on Christmas Eve,
when I want to get rid
of Richard's mom,

09:47.830 --> 09:49.620
I bring out a picture
of her at my age.

09:49.620 --> 09:52.210
We look exactly the same.
Creeps everybody out.

09:52.210 --> 09:53.960
She bolts, Richard can't
look at me for a month,

09:53.960 --> 09:55.000
everybody wins.

09:55.000 --> 09:57.330
You know, when I was a kid,

09:57.330 --> 10:00.040
they fought about decorating
the Christmas tree.

10:00.040 --> 10:02.790
He wanted big, blinking,
colorful lights,

10:02.790 --> 10:05.380
and she thought anything
but white bulbs was stupid.

10:05.380 --> 10:06.420
But I thought you said
Christmas morning

10:06.420 --> 10:08.250
was the happiest time
for your family.

10:08.250 --> 10:10.750
It was, once I got the idea
to have two trees --

10:10.750 --> 10:12.960
one for him and one for her.

10:12.960 --> 10:15.380
Because that's what a
9-year-old needs to worry
about at Christmas --

10:15.380 --> 10:17.460
keeping Mom and Dad
from fighting.

10:17.460 --> 10:20.670
So your answer lies in that
one tree in your living room.
Exactly.

10:20.670 --> 10:23.000
I'll just use the spirit
and wonder of the holidays

10:23.000 --> 10:26.080
to pit my parents against
each other and break 'em up.

10:26.080 --> 10:27.250
Aww.

10:27.250 --> 10:32.250
♪♪

10:32.250 --> 10:33.790
Here she comes.

10:35.580 --> 10:39.170
♪♪

10:40.620 --> 10:45.670
♪♪

10:45.670 --> 10:46.960
[ Gasps ]

10:46.960 --> 10:48.000
Oh, my God.

10:49.460 --> 10:51.040
Go get her, kid.
[ Exhales sharply ]

10:51.040 --> 10:53.290
What's that?

10:53.290 --> 10:54.880
It's a Tiffany
Infinity Bracelet,

10:54.880 --> 10:56.210
but there's no card,

10:56.210 --> 10:58.210
so it's from a Secret Santa,
I guess.

10:58.210 --> 11:00.210
I love it!
[ Chuckles ]

11:00.210 --> 11:01.380
Merry Christmas!

11:01.380 --> 11:02.540
It's from you?

11:02.540 --> 11:04.880
Whoa. He got her
the same present?

11:04.880 --> 11:07.170
He didn't get her
the same present,

11:07.170 --> 11:08.420
he just took credit
for yours.

11:10.120 --> 11:11.880
And now he's getting
my hug?

11:11.880 --> 11:14.080
I have to tell her.
No.

11:14.080 --> 11:16.290
Remember last time you told her
that Pierce was a jerk?

11:16.290 --> 11:18.330
You ended up
looking like the jerk.

11:18.330 --> 11:19.540
So I just give up?

11:23.040 --> 11:24.790
No.

11:24.790 --> 11:26.880
We need to come up
with a Secret Santa gift

11:26.880 --> 11:28.750
she'll know is from you.

11:28.750 --> 11:32.040
Then, when Pierce takes credit
for it, he's busted.

11:32.040 --> 11:34.170
So,
all we have to do is --

11:34.170 --> 11:35.710
I have an idea, but let's see
if yours is better.

11:35.710 --> 11:37.040
It has to be
something romantic.

11:38.670 --> 11:40.290
What did you guys do
on your first date?

11:40.290 --> 11:42.250
Oh, so, we went bowling
and we made up

11:42.250 --> 11:43.830
funny names for each other
to put on the screen.

11:43.830 --> 11:45.170
So she was "Lois Lane,"

11:45.170 --> 11:47.790
and I was
"Insert Player Two Name Here."

11:47.790 --> 11:49.500
Keyboard
was very confusing.

11:49.500 --> 11:50.920
That's it!

11:50.920 --> 11:53.250
Get her a bowling shirt
with "Lois Lane" on it.

11:53.250 --> 11:56.330
Whoa. Anna-Kat, you're like
a mini guidance counselor.

11:56.330 --> 11:58.170
Except you don't put Sambuca
in your coffee

11:58.170 --> 11:59.670
every time I walk
in your office.

12:02.790 --> 12:04.830
Come on, let's wrap it up.
What's the rush?

12:04.830 --> 12:06.000
I just want to get
the tree trimmed

12:06.000 --> 12:07.710
before Oliver's dance recital.

12:07.710 --> 12:09.080
So you're at peace with your
parents getting back together?

12:09.080 --> 12:10.670
Oh, yeah.

12:10.670 --> 12:12.500
I don't love
that "Oh, yeah."

12:12.500 --> 12:14.170
I've heard it before.
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

12:14.170 --> 12:15.250
Katie, you're still
on the pill, right?

12:17.170 --> 12:18.830
Oh, yeah.

12:18.830 --> 12:21.330
[ Chuckles ]
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

12:21.330 --> 12:22.500
Why are you guys
looking at me?

12:25.710 --> 12:27.040
Sorry we're late.

12:27.040 --> 12:29.620
I was just giving the Mouse King
a once-over.

12:29.620 --> 12:30.920
I got one, too.
[ Chuckles ]

12:30.920 --> 12:32.580
-Ugh.
-Here you go.

12:32.580 --> 12:34.000
Wow.

12:34.000 --> 12:36.540
It looks like nobody
has ever had sex on it!

12:36.540 --> 12:40.000
Well, the tree
is all decorated.

12:40.000 --> 12:41.290
What do you think?

12:41.290 --> 12:43.170
-It's very pretty. Yeah.
-That's nice.

12:43.170 --> 12:45.460
You sure?
Nothing that bothers you?

12:45.460 --> 12:47.750
Dad, you've always been
a star man, right?

12:47.750 --> 12:49.330
You sure you want
that angel up there?

12:49.330 --> 12:51.210
Well, nothing
to fight over.

12:51.210 --> 12:52.920
An angel is just fine.

12:52.920 --> 12:55.670
Like your entire life
was "just fine"

12:55.670 --> 12:57.670
after Mom chewed you up
and spit you out

12:57.670 --> 12:58.830
like a bad pistachio.

13:00.710 --> 13:02.290
Katie,
what are you doing?

13:02.290 --> 13:04.580
Just cherishing
a magical Christmas

13:04.580 --> 13:06.620
with both of my parents.

13:06.620 --> 13:09.330
Am I still allowed to do that,
Greg, or is this Russia?

13:09.330 --> 13:10.830
Mom, what do you think
of the lights?

13:10.830 --> 13:13.790
They sure are big and colorful
and blinkey.

13:13.790 --> 13:15.880
Well, I know they make
your father happy.

13:15.880 --> 13:17.830
Since when did you care
about that?

13:17.830 --> 13:18.920
My whole childhood,

13:18.920 --> 13:21.290
you lived off of menthols
and Dad's misery.

13:21.290 --> 13:22.580
Why are we bringing
this up now?

13:22.580 --> 13:24.000
I don't know.
It's the holidays.

13:24.000 --> 13:26.460
And it's nice to take a walk
down Memory Lane.

13:26.460 --> 13:29.040
Katie --
Remember how you'd tell Dad
to take 'em off,

13:29.040 --> 13:31.830
and he'd refuse and tell you,
"You're not gonna be happy

13:31.830 --> 13:34.460
until there were two more balls
hanging from the tree."

13:34.460 --> 13:36.620
Ornaments, Anna-Kat.

13:36.620 --> 13:39.210
She's, uh, talking
about ornaments.

13:39.210 --> 13:41.710
Mom realizes she's doing this
in front of her children.

13:41.710 --> 13:43.920
Isn't that right, Mama?
Remember how you'd rip
the lights off the tree

13:43.920 --> 13:44.620
and throw them at Dad?

13:44.620 --> 13:45.920
That was fun.

13:45.920 --> 13:47.290
Do you want to give them
a little tug?

13:47.290 --> 13:49.080
Katie, stop.
Now, the lights are fine.

13:49.080 --> 13:50.460
I know that you hate them.

13:50.460 --> 13:52.960
Here! Let me help you
pull them off!

13:52.960 --> 13:54.920
[ Ornaments shattering ]

13:54.920 --> 13:57.250
Oh, good, now I'm not
the only one in class

13:57.250 --> 13:59.290
whose mom hasn't had
a nervous breakdown.

13:59.290 --> 14:01.080
Thanks, Mom.
You've given me a lot to draw on

14:01.080 --> 14:03.620
when I play the villain
in "The Nutcracker."
Can we go do that now?

14:03.620 --> 14:05.040
Why aren't you two fighting
about the tree?!

14:05.040 --> 14:06.500
This is your tradition!

14:06.500 --> 14:08.040
I think I'll start
my own tradition

14:08.040 --> 14:09.460
by spending Christmas
at a friend's house.

14:11.250 --> 14:13.250
[ Screams ]

14:13.250 --> 14:14.830
[ Sighs ]

14:14.830 --> 14:16.120
My Mouse King mask!

14:19.460 --> 14:21.420
This was your peaceful
Christmas?

14:21.420 --> 14:23.420
What's your idea for
a happy New Year? The Purge?

14:25.380 --> 14:27.330
Look what you did.

14:32.790 --> 14:34.040
[ Remix of Tchaikovsky's "Dance
of the Sugar Plum Fairy" plays ]

14:35.960 --> 14:38.210
[ Indistinct conversations ]

14:39.460 --> 14:41.120
Hey, hey, hey.

14:41.120 --> 14:43.290
Relax.
It's gonna be fine.

14:43.290 --> 14:46.250
Oh, yeah, I'm on in half
an hour, and I have no mask.
Don't worry.

14:46.250 --> 14:48.330
You can fix anything
with duct tape.

14:48.330 --> 14:49.670
Why are you so upset?

14:49.670 --> 14:50.880
Your parents are
falling in love again --

14:50.880 --> 14:51.920
on Christmas.

14:51.920 --> 14:53.210
[ Katie sighs ]

14:53.210 --> 14:55.830
Add a rescue dog,
maybe Tori Spelling,

14:55.830 --> 14:58.290
you've got yourself
the perfect TV holiday movie.

14:58.290 --> 14:59.500
You're just pushing her
on my dad

14:59.500 --> 15:01.210
because you want her
out of your office.

15:01.210 --> 15:02.420
He's going to get
hurt again.

15:02.420 --> 15:03.880
You don't know that.
Yes, I do.

15:03.880 --> 15:05.960
I know my mom, and she's
gonna eat him alive.

15:05.960 --> 15:07.830
She is like a lake
full of piranhas,

15:07.830 --> 15:09.670
and he is like...

15:09.670 --> 15:12.170
something that falls into
a lake full of piranhas.

15:12.170 --> 15:13.710
A small cow?
Thank you.

15:13.710 --> 15:15.290
He's like a small cow.

15:15.290 --> 15:17.750
[ Music continues ]

15:17.750 --> 15:19.040
[ Conversations continue ]

15:22.330 --> 15:29.960
♪♪

15:31.540 --> 15:32.960
All right.

15:32.960 --> 15:35.210
The elf is delivering
the bowling shirt.

15:35.210 --> 15:38.000
Taylor will open it up and know
it can only be from you.

15:38.000 --> 15:39.460
Pierce will try to take credit.

15:39.460 --> 15:40.960
And she'll know he's a liar.

15:40.960 --> 15:42.750
Then you pop out,
kiss-kiss...

15:42.750 --> 15:43.880
And then we green-light

15:43.880 --> 15:44.790
"Real Horsewives" Season Two.

15:48.920 --> 15:50.540
I got her tickets?

15:50.540 --> 15:53.080
No, you bought her
a bowling shirt.

15:55.460 --> 15:57.210
I thought you'd want to go

15:57.210 --> 15:58.670
since you're gonna be
on Broadway someday.

15:58.670 --> 16:00.540
Oh, my God, thank you!

16:00.540 --> 16:02.080
What is going on?

16:02.080 --> 16:03.790
That tall guy over there
gave me 20 bucks

16:03.790 --> 16:05.620
to come over here and say,
"Thanks for the box."

16:07.170 --> 16:08.330
Pierce!

16:12.330 --> 16:14.170
Dad...
Hmm?

16:14.170 --> 16:17.420
...you and Mom
shouldn't be together.

16:17.420 --> 16:19.540
Look, kiddo, I can take care
of myself.

16:19.540 --> 16:21.170
Mom is just
making nice with you

16:21.170 --> 16:23.540
because she doesn't have
anywhere else to go.

16:23.540 --> 16:26.920
She is broke and looking for
a soft place to land.

16:26.920 --> 16:28.290
What are you saying?

16:28.290 --> 16:31.170
You are like a drywall screw
and she's a driver.

16:31.170 --> 16:34.620
And then she's going to use you
until your head gets stripped,

16:34.620 --> 16:36.380
and then she's gonna
leave you

16:36.380 --> 16:38.380
for one of those
fancy Torx screws.

16:40.330 --> 16:41.580
Now I understand.

16:41.580 --> 16:43.000
Mm-hmm.

16:43.000 --> 16:44.750
But maybe she --
Dad...

16:44.750 --> 16:48.000
I know you think
that you can fix anything,

16:48.000 --> 16:49.250
but you cannot fix her.

16:51.580 --> 16:52.750
Mnh-mnh.

16:52.750 --> 16:57.040
♪♪

16:59.790 --> 17:03.120
♪♪

17:05.170 --> 17:06.540
[ Quietly ] Your father
just told me

17:06.540 --> 17:08.250
he doesn't want me
to move in with him anymore

17:08.250 --> 17:10.120
and that he's
leaving tonight.

17:10.120 --> 17:12.420
What did you say
to him?

17:12.420 --> 17:14.500
[ Whispering ]
All of this is a bad idea.

17:14.500 --> 17:16.500
[ Scoffs ] And who are you
to say it's a bad idea?

17:16.500 --> 17:18.420
-Ugh.
-Shh!

17:18.420 --> 17:19.960
[ Sighs ]
We will finish
this conversation

17:19.960 --> 17:21.540
after Oliver's
performance.

17:21.540 --> 17:23.040
-Shh!
-I was just telling her

17:23.040 --> 17:25.080
that we need to stop talking.
Shh.

17:25.080 --> 17:26.790
Did you ask Santa for a
roundhouse kick to the teeth?

17:26.790 --> 17:27.580
'Cause you're about
to get it.

17:27.580 --> 17:31.670
♪♪

17:34.080 --> 17:36.920
You're on in 15 seconds.

17:36.920 --> 17:38.420
There you are.
Did you fix it?

17:38.420 --> 17:40.500
Well, I'm not gonna use
the phrase "as good as new"...

17:42.960 --> 17:46.000
Uh, yeah, how's that?

17:46.000 --> 17:47.080
[ Muffled ]
Not great.

17:47.080 --> 17:48.880
You're on!
Go, go!

17:48.880 --> 17:55.040
♪♪

17:57.290 --> 17:58.540
[ Audience gasps ]

17:58.540 --> 17:59.920
Oh, my God.

17:59.920 --> 18:01.880
I guess we can finish
that conversation now.

18:05.460 --> 18:08.170
You need to get your nose
out of our business.

18:08.170 --> 18:09.540
Why do you care
what we do?

18:09.540 --> 18:11.830
I am not letting you chew him up
and spit him out

18:11.830 --> 18:12.880
like you did before.

18:12.880 --> 18:14.210
What the hell
do you know?

18:14.210 --> 18:16.460
Lots!
I grew up in that house!

18:16.460 --> 18:18.580
-Shh!
-Ugh! We're in a lobby!

18:18.580 --> 18:21.710
I admit that things went south
between me and your dad,

18:21.710 --> 18:23.500
but we wanted
different things.

18:23.500 --> 18:25.380
That is not gonna happen
this time.

18:25.380 --> 18:26.460
Based on what?!

18:26.460 --> 18:27.710
Living with you!

18:29.920 --> 18:31.380
Huh?

18:31.380 --> 18:34.250
Living with you and Greg
these past few months,

18:34.250 --> 18:36.670
I've watched how you two
work together.

18:36.670 --> 18:38.830
I mean, you're -- you're totally
different, but -- but...

18:38.830 --> 18:40.750
[ Scoffs ] I don't know.
You figure it out.

18:40.750 --> 18:42.920
You talk things through.

18:42.920 --> 18:45.580
You don't have a fight
and then fly off to another city

18:45.580 --> 18:47.920
to do tequila shots
with Jan-Michael Vincent.

18:47.920 --> 18:49.210
[ Sighs ]

18:49.210 --> 18:51.330
You taught me
what marriage is.

18:51.330 --> 18:52.790
[ Chuckles ]

18:52.790 --> 18:54.670
I mean, I...

18:54.670 --> 18:58.000
I didn't get it the first time
around with your dad, but...

18:58.000 --> 19:00.120
I think I get it now.

19:00.120 --> 19:02.670
♪♪

19:06.330 --> 19:08.420
There you go.

19:08.420 --> 19:10.380
Good as new.
And that's a watertight seal.

19:10.380 --> 19:12.460
You don't even need a shoe.
Thanks, Grandpa.

19:12.460 --> 19:14.620
[ Quietly ] We're still going
to the hospital, right?

19:14.620 --> 19:15.620
Oh, yeah.

19:15.620 --> 19:16.830
Oh.
[ Sighs ]

19:16.830 --> 19:18.040
-Dad?
-Yeah.

19:18.040 --> 19:19.620
I'd like you
to meet somebody.

19:19.620 --> 19:21.290
Her name is Kathryn.

19:21.290 --> 19:23.710
I'm not gonna lie --
she's a lot,

19:23.710 --> 19:26.790
but I think you'd make
a great couple.

19:26.790 --> 19:27.830
[ Kathryn chuckles ]

19:27.830 --> 19:29.330
You were right.

19:29.330 --> 19:31.170
This would make
a good holiday movie.

19:31.170 --> 19:32.290
Shh!

19:32.290 --> 19:33.580
Excuse me.

19:33.580 --> 19:35.420
I'm going to be in jail
for Christmas.

19:35.420 --> 19:41.500
♪♪

19:41.500 --> 19:48.040
♪♪

19:48.040 --> 19:51.210
Despite my worst efforts,
everyone got what they wanted.

19:51.210 --> 19:53.380
I got my peaceful Christmas.

19:53.380 --> 19:55.000
Greg is getting
his office back.

19:55.000 --> 19:57.210
Taylor got that
over-priced bracelet,

19:57.210 --> 19:59.210
not to mention theater tickets
and a new boyfriend.

19:59.210 --> 20:01.710
Anna-Kat seems pretty excited

20:01.710 --> 20:04.080
about that portable belt sander
my dad got her.

20:04.080 --> 20:06.460
My mom got her soft landing.

20:06.460 --> 20:09.330
Even Oliver kind of got
what he wanted --

20:09.330 --> 20:11.000
to be the star of the show.

20:11.000 --> 20:12.830
[ Laughs ]
They looped it!

20:12.830 --> 20:13.830
Oliver: Aah!

20:13.830 --> 20:15.380
Aah!
Aah!

20:15.380 --> 20:18.000
3,000 likes?!

20:18.000 --> 20:20.460
We need to make a follow-up
right away.

20:20.460 --> 20:22.580
What do you think of
"Mouse King tries to dunk

20:22.580 --> 20:24.540
and pulls the hoop down
on top of himself?"

20:24.540 --> 20:25.500
[ Laughs ]

20:33.040 --> 20:34.750
[ As Donatella Morningstar ] She
wasn't invited, so I was all,

20:34.750 --> 20:37.670
"Filly, don't get in my muzzle
with your cheap extensions!"

20:37.670 --> 20:39.710
[ Laughs ]

20:39.710 --> 20:41.540
[ As Sparkles O'Donahue ]
You just broke the nasty
meter, Donatella.

20:41.540 --> 20:43.210
No one wants you here,
Sparkles.

20:43.210 --> 20:45.710
Your bloodline
has no champions.

20:45.710 --> 20:48.250
[ As pony ] Not for nothing,
but I hear your grandmother

20:48.250 --> 20:50.000
was sired by a donkey.

20:50.000 --> 20:51.210
You two are just jealous

20:51.210 --> 20:53.040
because my bridle
has diamonds on it,

20:53.040 --> 20:55.710
and my horseshoes
cost more than your stables.

20:57.500 --> 21:00.420
[ As Donatella ] Get out before
I bite you in the withers!

21:00.420 --> 21:01.880
[ Normal voice ]
Is that the butt?

21:01.880 --> 21:04.250
[ Normal voice ]
[ Laughing ] No, the neck!

21:04.250 --> 21:05.960
[ Chuckles ]
Drama and education --

21:05.960 --> 21:07.210
this show has everything.

21:07.210 --> 21:08.920
[ Laughs ]
